      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The consensus on whether capital gains changes will *definitively* drive the wealth gap up is currently lacking. Proponents of the high-earner benefit argue that lower capital gains rates encourage investment, which theoretically benefits the broader economy. Critics, however, contend that preferential treatment for asset income disproportionately benefits the wealthy, allowing them to accumulate capital faster than wage earners. Ultimately, the real-world effect depends heavily on how these changes interact with other aspects of the overall tax code.",
      "source": "target",
