    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you on the \"it depends\" part, but it feels like we can go a bit deeper. When you look at the actual data from similar past reforms, isn't it pretty well-documented that lowering capital gains rates tends to increase wealth concentration? Like, is it even a fair debate to call it \"benefiting the broader economy\" if the math shows the capital just sits at the top? I'm looking for a more definitive take on whether the inflationary/inequality risks actually outweigh the investment arguments.",
